social_posts.post_text: Had this song stuck in my head for weeks now! Had to do something about it ✨
Can’t tell how many times I listened to this song. Since I was a kid, huge inspiration for the singer and songwriter I am today ☺️✨

Lost in a Roman wilderness of pain
And all the children are insane
All the children are insane
Waiting for the summer rain

Recently, I’ve been going through old songs I wrote and recorded. It’s crazy how I’ve always focused on the flaws and things that I could have done better everytime I listen to myself. 
One thing that is definitely a big challenge for me is my accent, as English isn’t my first language. It will probably never be perfect, but I know that it keeps getting better. Work and time. 
I wanted to give a quick new shot to this amazing song I wrote with @iamtimecop1983 5 years ago now! Time flies so fast. I still love it so much.

Everytime I go back where I’m from, I feel the need to capture the beauty and ephemerality of moments of love and happiness. My heart is full of joy and nostalgia looking at those pictures, even though it was just a few weeks ago.

A few shots from my last roll. Unedited. I had to open the camera mid-roll cause it got stuck somehow, and what happened on those shots is pretty crazy. I love it. Very unique.

(Last shot is there just cause it’s France)

Had the best time with my best friend @chapitre.30 • in a very special place. 
Just sharing a few shots, but it can’t translate the beauty and diversity of those islands, the food, the beaches, the jungle, the volcanos, everything is so inspiring. 
Tell me about your summer ✨
